Talaat, Palm Hills Advance After Report on New Property Law

-- B y   A h m e d   A   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-05-26T14:42:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-26/palm-hills-talaat-advance-after-report-on-new-property-law.html
Talaat Moustafa Group (TMGH)  Holding led
gains among  Egypt ’s real-estate developers after  Al Masry Al
Youm  reported the government is studying a law that may shield
investors from prosecution for illegal land purchases under
previous governments.  Shares of Egypt’s biggest publicly listed developer jumped
4.3 percent to 4.43 Egyptian pounds at the 2:30 p.m. close in
Cairo, the highest level in seven weeks.  Palm Hills Developments
SAE (PHDC) , the nation’s second-largest publicly traded developer,
climbed 2.8 percent to 2.17 pounds, the highest level since
April 14.  The proposed legislation would hold previous governments
accountable for violating rules by selling land via direct
orders and not through public auctions, the Cairo-based
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  